<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-03-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-03-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="584" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d584">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 337.11/264</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-03-13">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 13, 1917</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Francisco Sugar Company, 112 Wall Street, New York, states that cane
                            burnt on their property represents loss of over 2,200,000 dollars. They
                            request further protection for their property, and are filing claim
                            against Government of Cuba. Bring this matter attention of President
                            Menocal and request Cuban Government give protection to this
                            property.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>